<td colspan=3 class=black><br><p><font class=b>Objective</font><br><font class=black>
Bounce out balls by arranging them in lines of three or more of the same color. You can swap two balls that are next to each other (touching), but at least one of the balls must form a line of three or more balls of the same color. You receive more points for getting four, five or more balls at the same time. You also receive bonus points if other balls line up and bounce out as a result of your move (in a chain-reaction). To move on to the next level of play, you must remove the required number of balls, as indicated in the "Balls To Go" field, before time runs out on the fuse. Those ominous black balls are bad news. Can't click 'em, can't lick em. Use the Mouse to click on the balls to select them. Selecting a selected ball unselects it. Got that? Now go play!
























































































































































































































































































